    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>into thin wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/camembert-xmas-dirty-fries-with-pigs-in-blankets/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>parsnip[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then into batons</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into batons</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/camembert-xmas-dirty-fries-with-pigs-in-blankets/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chips</strong>, <strong>pigs in blankets</strong>, <strong>onion wedges</strong>,<strong> parsnip and carrot batons </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 25 min or until beginning to golden and crisp</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/camembert-xmas-dirty-fries-with-pigs-in-blankets/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/camembert-xmas-dirty-fries-with-pigs-in-blankets/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>camembert[s] </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/camembert-xmas-dirty-fries-with-pigs-in-blankets/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>gravy base</strong> and <strong>cranberry sauce</strong> to a measuring jug with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Put it in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 1 min \u2013 this is your <strong>cranberry gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/camembert-xmas-dirty-fries-with-pigs-in-blankets/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Push the chips, pigs in blankets and root veg into 1 pile per person, then top with the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>camembert cheese</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 6-7 min or until the cheese has melted \u2013 these are your <strong>camembert Xmas dirty fries with pigs in blankets</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/camembert-xmas-dirty-fries-with-pigs-in-blankets/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>camembert Xmas dirty fries with pigs and blankets</strong>,<strong> </strong>and drizzle the <strong>cranberry gravy </strong>over the top</p><p>Top with the <strong>chopped chives</strong> and your <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
